  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. Substituting <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the ordered pair 1 comma 1\"></span> into the inequality gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"5 times 1, minus, 3 times 1, is less than 4\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 is less than 4\"></span>, which is a true statement. Substituting <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the ordered pair 2 comma 5\"></span> into the inequality gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"5 times 2, minus, 3 times 5, is less than 4\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 5 is less than 4\"></span>, which is a true statement. Substituting <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the ordered pair 3 comma 2\"></span> into the inequality gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"5 times 3, minus, 3 times 2, is less than 4\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"9 is less than 4\"></span>, which is not a true statement. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the ordered pair 1 comma 1\"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the ordered pair 2 comma 5\"></span> are the only ordered pairs shown that satisfy the given inequality.<p>Choice A is incorrect because the ordered pair <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 comma 5\"></span> also satisfies the inequality. Choice B is incorrect because the ordered pair <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"1 comma 1\"></span> also satisfies the inequality. Choice D is incorrect because the ordered pair <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 comma 2\"></span> does not satisfy the inequality.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
